<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
TYPE: staircase_or_linear
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.staircase_or_linear">


The <b>staircase_or_linear</b> type specifies the interpolation method for
colours in a <express_ref linkend="presentation_resource_schema:ir_express:presentation_resource_schema.colour_association_table"/>. 






</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: staircase_or_linear.linear
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.staircase_or_linear.linear"> The colours are interpolated linearly. </ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: staircase_or_linear.staircase
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.staircase_or_linear.staircase"> The colours are interpolated using a staircase function. 
  </ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
TYPE: presentable_text
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.presentable_text">


A <b>presentable_text</b> is any string which can be presented. 






<example>IP1 prohibits linefeed and carriage return characters
  in <b>presentable_text</b>.</example>

</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: presentable_text.wr:IP1
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.presentable_text.wr:IP1"> The string shall not contain any control characters.</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
TYPE: font_select
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.font_select">


The <b>font_select</b> is used for the definition of <express_ref linkend="presentation_definition_schema:ir_express:presentation_definition_schema.text_literal"/>s
and <express_ref linkend="presentation_resource_schema:ir_express:presentation_resource_schema.character_glyph_symbol"/>s. It selects between different sources
for text fonts.
 


</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
ENTITY: character_glyph_symbol
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.character_glyph_symbol">


A <b>character_glyph_symbol</b> contains the geometric representation of a 
character. 







% ?????? 

<note>Figure <module_ref linkend="presentation_resource_schema:4_entities:figure:fig_font_family">fig_font_family</module_ref> illustrates the types and definition of
       character glyph symbols.</note>

</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: character_glyph_symbol.wr:WR2
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.character_glyph_symbol.wr:WR2"> The <b>box_height</b> shall be a <express_ref linkend="measure_schema:ir_express:measure_schema.positive_length_measure"/>.</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: character_glyph_symbol.box_height
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.character_glyph_symbol.box_height"> the height of the <b>character_box</b>.</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: character_glyph_symbol.baseline_ratio
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.character_glyph_symbol.baseline_ratio"> the location of the baseline of the character glyph
relative to the <b>character_box</b>. When character glyphs are composed to 
form a text literal, the baselines of adjacent glyphs are aligned. The 
character baseline is parallel to the x axis of the <b>character_box</b>. 
The specified value indicates the distance between the x axis of the 
<b>character_box</b> and the baseline as ratio of <b>box_height</b>.

<note>x axis and extent of the character box are defined by 
       <express_ref linkend="presentation_resource_schema:ir_express:presentation_resource_schema.planar_extent"/>, clause \ref{planar extent}.</note>

<example>A <b>baseline_ratio</b> of 0.0 specifies that the baseline of the 
  character glyph and x axis are identical. A <b>baseline_ratio</b> of 0.5 
  specifies that the baseline of the character glyph divides the 
  <b>character_box</b> in the middle of its height.</example>

</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: character_glyph_symbol.character_box
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.character_glyph_symbol.character_box"> a rectangular box defining the extent of a character
glyph. The <b>character_box</b> can be slanted by the <express_ref linkend="presentation_appearance_schema:ir_express:presentation_appearance_schema.text_style"/>
to produce slanted character glyphs.

</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: character_glyph_symbol.wr:WR1
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.character_glyph_symbol.wr:WR1"> The <b>baseline_ratio</b> ranges between 0.0 and 1.0.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
ENTITY: character_glyph_symbol_stroke
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.character_glyph_symbol_stroke">


A <b>character_glyph_symbol_stroke</b> is a 
<express_ref linkend="presentation_resource_schema:ir_express:presentation_resource_schema.character_glyph_symbol"/> where the geometry of the glyph is described 
by a set of curves.









</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: character_glyph_symbol_stroke.strokes
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.character_glyph_symbol_stroke.strokes"> the set of <express_ref linkend="geometry_schema:ir_express:geometry_schema.curve"/>s that define the geometry of the
    character glyph.</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: character_glyph_symbol_stroke.wr:WR1
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.character_glyph_symbol_stroke.wr:WR1"> All the curves making up the character glyph shall be contained
    in the set of items.</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
ENTITY: character_glyph_symbol_outline
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.character_glyph_symbol_outline">


A <b>character_glyph_symbol_outline</b> is a 
<express_ref linkend="presentation_resource_schema:ir_express:presentation_resource_schema.character_glyph_symbol"/> where the geometry of the glyph is described 
by a set of <express_ref linkend="presentation_definition_schema:ir_express:presentation_definition_schema.annotation_fill_area"/>s.








</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: character_glyph_symbol_outline.outlines
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.character_glyph_symbol_outline.outlines"> the set of <express_ref linkend="presentation_definition_schema:ir_express:presentation_definition_schema.annotation_fill_area"/>s that define
    the geometry of the character glyph.</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: character_glyph_symbol_outline.wr:WR1
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.character_glyph_symbol_outline.wr:WR1"> All the fill areas making up the character glyph shall be 
    contained in the set of items.</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
ENTITY: character_glyph_font_usage
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.character_glyph_font_usage">


A <b>character_glyph_font_usage</b> specifies the participation of a 
<express_ref linkend="presentation_resource_schema:ir_express:presentation_resource_schema.character_glyph_symbol"/> in a <express_ref linkend="presentation_resource_schema:ir_express:presentation_resource_schema.text_font"/>.






</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: character_glyph_font_usage.character
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.character_glyph_font_usage.character"> the <express_ref linkend="presentation_resource_schema:ir_express:presentation_resource_schema.character_glyph_symbol"/> that is part of the font.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: character_glyph_font_usage.font
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.character_glyph_font_usage.font"> the <express_ref linkend="presentation_resource_schema:ir_express:presentation_resource_schema.text_font"/> to which the <express_ref linkend="presentation_resource_schema:ir_express:presentation_resource_schema.character_glyph_symbol"/> is assigned.</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
ENTITY: text_font
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.text_font">


A <b>text_font</b> is the identification of a specific character font.






<example>Examples for character fonts are Courier 12, Times 10, 
  Helvetica Bold 14, 0815, ABC.</example>

</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: text_font.description
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.text_font.description"> text that relates the nature of the <b>text_font</b>.
  </ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: text_font.glyphs
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.text_font.glyphs"> the set of <express_ref linkend="presentation_resource_schema:ir_express:presentation_resource_schema.character_glyph_font_usage"/>s that identify the 
<express_ref linkend="presentation_resource_schema:ir_express:presentation_resource_schema.character_glyph_symbol"/>s that participate in the <b>text_font</b>.</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: text_font.name
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.text_font.name"> the word, or group of words, by which the <b>text_font</b> is referred to. 
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: text_font.id
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.text_font.id"> the identification of the <b>text_font</b>.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
ENTITY: text_font_family
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.text_font_family">


A <b>text_font_family</b> is the identification of a related collection of <express_ref linkend="presentation_resource_schema:ir_express:presentation_resource_schema.text_font"/>s.






</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: text_font_family.description
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.text_font_family.description"> text that relates the nature of the <b>text_font_family</b>.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: text_font_family.name
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.text_font_family.name"> the word, or group of words, by which the <b>text_font_family</b> is referred to. </ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: text_font_family.fonts
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.text_font_family.fonts"> the set of <express_ref linkend="presentation_resource_schema:ir_express:presentation_resource_schema.text_font_in_family"/>s that identify the <express_ref linkend="presentation_resource_schema:ir_express:presentation_resource_schema.text_font"/>s that 
participate in the <b>text_font_family</b>.</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: text_font_family.id
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.text_font_family.id"> the identification of the <b>text_font_family</b>.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
ENTITY: text_font_in_family
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.text_font_in_family">


A <b>text_font_in_family</b> specifies the participation of a <express_ref linkend="presentation_resource_schema:ir_express:presentation_resource_schema.text_font"/> in a 
<express_ref linkend="presentation_resource_schema:ir_express:presentation_resource_schema.text_font_family"/>.






<example>Some font families are Courier and Helvetica. Fonts
in these families include Courier 12, Helvetica Bold 14, respectively.</example>

</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: text_font_in_family.family
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.text_font_in_family.family"> the <express_ref linkend="presentation_resource_schema:ir_express:presentation_resource_schema.text_font_family"/> to which the <express_ref linkend="presentation_resource_schema:ir_express:presentation_resource_schema.text_font"/> is assigned.</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: text_font_in_family.font
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.text_font_in_family.font"> the <express_ref linkend="presentation_resource_schema:ir_express:presentation_resource_schema.text_font"/> that is part of the family.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
ENTITY: externally_defined_text_font
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.externally_defined_text_font">


An <b>externally_defined_text_font</b> is an external reference to a 
text font. 




</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
ENTITY: pre_defined_text_font
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.pre_defined_text_font">


A <b>pre_defined_text_font</b> is a text font provided for the 
definition of an application--specific font.

<note>Application Resources or Application Protocols specify the use of 
this entity.</note>




</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
ENTITY: colour
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.colour">


A colour defines a basic appearance property of an element with respect to
the light reflected by it.




</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
ENTITY: colour_specification
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.colour_specification">


A <b>colour_specification</b> contains a colour definition which refers 
directly to a specific colour space.

<example>Colour spaces are RGB, HLS, HSV, and CIE. More 
  details about these colour spaces can be found in [12].</example>

<note>Only RGB colours are supported by this part of ISO~10303. This entity 
  provides for later extension.</note>






</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: colour_specification.name
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.colour_specification.name"> the word, or group of words, by which the <b>colour_specification</b> is referred to.}{O/E1}</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
ENTITY: colour_rgb
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.colour_rgb">


A colour\_\-rgb defines a colour by specifying the intensity of red, green,
and blue.








</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: colour_rgb.green
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.colour_rgb.green"> the intensity of the green colour component.

</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: colour_rgb.red
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.colour_rgb.red"> the intensity of the red colour component.

</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: colour_rgb.wr:WR2
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.colour_rgb.wr:WR2"> The intensity of the green component shall be between 0.0
and 1.0.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: colour_rgb.wr:WR3
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.colour_rgb.wr:WR3"> The intensity of the blue component shall be between 0.0
and 1.0.</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: colour_rgb.blue
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.colour_rgb.blue"> the intensity of the blue colour component.</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: colour_rgb.wr:WR1
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.colour_rgb.wr:WR1"> The intensity of the red colour component shall be between 0.0
and 1.0.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
ENTITY: colour_associated
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.colour_associated">


The <b>colour_associated</b> entity defines a colour for the visualization
of one--dimensional state variables to achieve a rendered picture. The colour 
at specific positions of a curve or surface is derived from the values of the 
state variables and the <express_ref linkend="presentation_resource_schema:ir_express:presentation_resource_schema.colour_association_table"/>. The positions 
for which the colours are derived depend on the 
<express_ref linkend="presentation_appearance_schema:ir_express:presentation_appearance_schema.shading_curve_method"/> or the <express_ref linkend="presentation_appearance_schema:ir_express:presentation_appearance_schema.shading_surface_method"/>
assigned to the curve or surface, respectively. The derived colours are 
interpolated according to the shading method appearance attribute.


  <note number="1">e variables are often used to specify physical quantities.
  </note><note number="2">interpolation of colours across curves and surfaces is described
  in ref{shading curve method} and ref{shading surface method}.</note>







</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: colour_associated.mapping
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.colour_associated.mapping"> the <express_ref linkend="presentation_resource_schema:ir_express:presentation_resource_schema.colour_association_table"/> used to derive the 
   colour.</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: colour_associated.variable_to_be_shown
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.colour_associated.variable_to_be_shown"> the set of state variables are the
one--dimensional values to be visualized by colours.

</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: colour_associated.name
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.colour_associated.name"> the word, or group of words, by which the colour_asscociated is referred to.}{O/E1}

</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
ENTITY: colour_association_table
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.colour_association_table">


A <b>colour_association_table</b> defines the mapping of a
one--dimensional state variable space into a colour
space.

The <b>colour_association_table</b> contains state variable values
that are associated with a colour. When the value of a state variable
is between two fixed state variable values, the colour shall be 
calculated by either staircase or linear interpolation.






</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: colour_association_table.interpolation_type
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.colour_association_table.interpolation_type"> the method of interpolation to be used.</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: colour_association_table.discrete_states_with_colours
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.colour_association_table.discrete_states_with_colours"> a list of 
one--dimensional state variable values that are associated with colour.

</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
ENTITY: state_variable_with_colour
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.state_variable_with_colour">


A <b>state_variable_with_colour</b> associates a single fixed
state variable with a <express_ref linkend="presentation_resource_schema:ir_express:presentation_resource_schema.colour_specification"/>.


 



</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: state_variable_with_colour.associated_colour
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.state_variable_with_colour.associated_colour"> the <express_ref linkend="presentation_resource_schema:ir_express:presentation_resource_schema.colour_specification"/> associated with
  the <b>state_variable</b>.</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: state_variable_with_colour.state_variable
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.state_variable_with_colour.state_variable"> the value of a one--dimensional 
<b>state_variable</b>.

  <example>Physical state variables are temperature and stress 
   components.</example>

</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
ENTITY: pre_defined_colour
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.pre_defined_colour">


A <b>pre_defined_colour</b> is provided to allow 
an application--specific colour definition.

<note>Application Resources or Application Protocols specify the use of 
       this entity.
       The <b>pre_defined_colour</b> entity further enables Application 
       Resources or Application Protocols to fix colour values or components
       of colour values for their particular uses.</note>




</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
ENTITY: planar_extent
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.planar_extent">


A <b>planar_extent</b> specifies an extent in both directions of a
two--dimensional coordinate system.






</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: planar_extent.size_in_y
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.planar_extent.size_in_y"> the extent in the y axis direction.</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: planar_extent.size_in_x
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.planar_extent.size_in_x"> the extent in the x axis direction.

  </ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
ENTITY: planar_box
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.planar_box">


A <b>planar_box</b> specifies an arbitrary rectangular box and its location 
in a two--dimensional cartesian coordinate system.






</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: planar_box.placement
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.planar_box.placement"> the position and orientation of the bottom--left corner of the box. The attributes of the supertype define the length of the sides of the box along the positive x and y axes.</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
ENTITY: presentation_scaled_placement
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.presentation_scaled_placement">


The <b>presentation_scaled_placement</b> is a 
<express_ref linkend="geometry_schema:ir_express:geometry_schema.geometric_representation_item"/> provided to support the definition
of <express_ref linkend="presentation_organization_schema:ir_express:presentation_organization_schema.graphical_transformation"/>s.

<note><express_ref linkend="presentation_organization_schema:ir_express:presentation_organization_schema.graphical_transformation"/> is defined in 
\ref{graphical transformation}.</note>







</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: presentation_scaled_placement.scaling
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.presentation_scaled_placement.scaling"> the scaling that is part of the transformation.</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: presentation_scaled_placement.placement
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.presentation_scaled_placement.placement"> a placement used to define rotation and translation.

  </ext_description>

</ext_descriptions>
